latestPosts.caption:
A moment I’ll never forget under the Cannes lights. 🌟
From a little girl with big dreams to walking the red carpet at Cannes—not once, but twice. Last year, I made history as the first Indian designer to walk this iconic carpet, and this year marked my second debut. Every step is a reminder that with faith, grit, and grace, dreams do come true. God is great. 🙏❤️
Took my brand on international level is such a dream I am living now ♥️

#Cannes2025 #FromDreamsToReality #ProudlyIndian

Dress designed by @labelnimisha

latestPosts.caption:
I feel emotional even while writing this because this time it was my 50th international show including Milan Fashion Week🤍

I have only done hard work since childhood with the hope that one day I will definitely get its fruits and that too so soon. I got everything at a very young age, responsibility, adulthood and success. But I have always remained grounded, those who know about me know that wherever I am.. I am still grounded to my roots🤍 

Thank you to my team who travels with me, has fun with me, parties with me and of course works with me🙈❤️

latestPosts.caption:
Two months, countless battles.
A fractured leg, a vein injury, hearing loss, and health scares that kept piling on, yet here I am. While hospitals became second homes, my spirit stayed rooted in one thing: the vision.
Late nights turned into dawns, designing what I dreamed not just outfits, but stories. This year, Cannes wasn’t just about representing India, it was about bringing to life the delicate poetry of spring through 3D floral designs, crafted with every ounce of strength I had left.
To my incredible team and staff — thank you. This wasn’t easy, but together, we turned pain into purpose. 🌸✨
Resilience is the real runway.
.
.
.
